

Albert & Margaret Alkek Foundation







































Albert 
                    B. Alkek created a living legacy in the wording of his last 
                    will and testament. In it, he laid out a road map that created 
                    the Albert and Margaret Alkek Foundation. Upon his death, 
                    in 1995, the Foundation took up the work to which Mr. Alkek 
                    and his family had devoted considerable thought, energy and 
                    wealth. The Foundation continues to provide support for charitable, 
                    religious, scientific (primarily medical), cultural and educational 
                    organizations and programs serving the people of the state 
                    of Texas. 
The 
                    majority of the Foundation’s grants reflect Mr. Alkek’s 
                    preferences for research 
                    and education-related projects that will pay lasting dividends 
                    in terms of new discoveries and improved quality of life. 
                    Additional grants reflect the Alkek family’s strong 
                    community involvement, both in Houston and throughout the 
                    state. 

















